full_text: A transaction or job is out of sequence if its effective date is earlier than other bound transactions on the policy for that contractual term. In this example, a customer calls to change a car's color in an auto policy, effective on March 1st. Later, the customer calls to make some changes effective on February 1st. Click Actions. Create the first policy change. Set the effective date of the policy change to March 1st, using the calendar. Click Next to start the policy change process. Go to Vehicles. Change the car's color to yellow. Go to PIA Coverages. Medical limit is changed to 10,000. Quote the policy change. Issue the policy. Go back to the same policy file. The customer calls again to say that he had the car painted blue. And added a new driver on February 1st. Start the second policy change job. Set the effective date to February 1st, which is earlier than the previous policy change job. Click Next to start the process. Click OK to proceed. The out of sequence message is displayed on the top of every page. Go to Drivers. Add a new driver. Create a new driver. Simply select an existing driver. Click the Roles tab. Make sure to populate the fields for year first licensed and the number of accidents and violations. Go to Vehicles. Change the vehicle's color to blue. Go to PIA Coverages. The customer also wants to select a higher medical limit. Select 20,000. Try to quote.  An error message is displayed for an out of sequence conflict that requires resolution. Go to Policy Review. Click Change Conflicts. The conflicts occur when changes are made to the same fields. In this example, the color and medical limit. The newly added driver does not cause any conflict because the change is not on the same field. You can click the Override All or Override None buttons. You can also resolve individual conflict by selecting Yes or No in the Override Future Conflicts column. In this example, click No for the car's color, so that the color is not on the same field. The color blue of the current job is only effective from February 1st to March 1st. On March 1st, the color yellow from the other job will be effective for the policy, while the liability limit will be merged forward to the job with a later effective date. Click Submit. After submitting the resolution, it cannot be reverted. Click OK to confirm. Now you can quote the policy change. Issue the policy. This is the end of demonstration of out of sequence transaction.
